from the fjords of norway to barren windswept iceland to the 
hightech affluence of sweden john pauls tour was unlike any of 
his previous trips to christian countries even those like britain 
where roman catholics are a minority 
faced with some reluctance to the visit by lutheran clergy the 
leader of the worlds 850 million roman catholics agreed to sit in 
