<TEXT>
two faces of the rocky flats nuclear plant were 
presented by its operators and its federal overseers an affidavit 
and internal memos revealed after federal raids shut down the 
facility as unsafe last week 
hazardous wastes were burned illegally in a plutonium 
reprocessing building while it was closed for safety violations the 
affidavit states yet the department of energy paid rocky flats 
managers bonuses each year as rewards for production and management 
a july 1986 energy department internal memorandum said rocky 
flats was in poor condition generally in terms of environmental 
compliance and its permit applications were grossly deficient 
the memo also indicated some of the plants waste facilities were 
patently illegal plutonium triggers are made at the plant 
northwest of denver 
yet an ad for rockwell international the facilitys operator 
appears in the current edition of a metropolitan weekly the 
broomfield enterprise inviting the public to tour the plant 
officials said the tours were the companys method of explaining to 
neighboring communities how the nuclear weapons plant operated and 
why 
